1
00:00:00,885 --> 00:00:06,169
Det här är en av våra, och nästan alla är en del av den gigantiska historien om Air Force-försök i den här kriget.

2
00:00:06,190 --> 00:00:13,096
Och när vi flyger över till Sir Arthur Cunningham, under som de allierade Air Forces har gjort så här fantastiska jobb, och general Alexander, deputat av C&C i Norra Afrika.

3
00:00:13,117 --> 00:00:13,596
Det är en krig.

4
00:00:26,434 --> 00:00:32,896
We anticipate our entry into Tunis by showing some of the damage our bombers did to dumps and harbor installations and communications.

5
00:00:33,438 --> 00:00:36,579
It's not always easy to imagine what damage our bombing does to the enemy.

6
00:00:36,878 --> 00:00:38,219
Here, therefore, is some of it.

7
00:00:39,140 --> 00:00:43,042
Now, would anyone like to rent a small furnished flat conveniently situated on the roar?

8
00:00:44,963 --> 00:00:46,103
Following up the air bombardment...

9
00:01:57,823 --> 00:01:58,183
Välkommen tillbaka!

10
00:03:19,889 --> 00:03:20,049
Varsågod!

11
00:04:22,762 --> 00:04:24,824
The first real taste of the fruits of victory for the little man who's often been down.

12
00:04:24,843 --> 00:04:25,543
But never and never will be out.

13
00:04:54,456 --> 00:04:56,677
Churchill tanks on the road from Pichon, striking east to Carouan and Sousse.

14
00:04:56,697 --> 00:04:58,598
The first armies attack coinciding with the 8th armies drive up north to Sfax.

15
00:05:27,632 --> 00:05:31,435
Det här var positionen i början av april med fängelser som kom in när vårt armé var framöver.

16
00:05:32,055 --> 00:05:35,697
Amerikansk och fransk trupper spelade också en viktig del i dessa krig.

17
00:05:35,716 --> 00:05:37,999
Några av dessa fängelser hade bara varit i Tunisia i tio dagar.

18
00:05:56,589 --> 00:06:00,312
Engineers once again worked like heroes to facilitate the advance of the forward units.

19
00:06:08,057 --> 00:06:11,781
Overhead on all sectors the RAF and allied air forces gave strong support.

20
00:06:12,161 --> 00:06:17,285
Much appreciated by the men on the ground.

21
00:06:17,305 --> 00:06:20,127
A Sherman tank in action with the 8th army on the drive to Sfax.

22
00:06:25,204 --> 00:06:28,786
Bräderna hade blivit stjärnade av den uttryckande kvinnan, men den stora tröjan stannade inte.

23
00:06:28,805 --> 00:06:45,771
Hållbarhetsstationen visar svårighetsbevis på de steg vi tog för att hindra germansk transport.

24
00:06:45,810 --> 00:06:48,531
Och på morgonen den 9 april kom den 8a armén till Sfax.

25
00:06:49,031 --> 00:06:52,894
Räddningen bland alla invånare berättar bara om deras räddning för att de hade drivits ut.

26
00:07:22,240 --> 00:07:27,923
A great day for Sfax and for British, American and French troops whose flags now flew proudly side by side.

27
00:07:33,925 --> 00:07:36,348
General Montgomery here as always had a great reception.

28
00:07:55,151 --> 00:07:59,353
Den åttonde armén har fått en flygfortress som en gift från amerikanerna.

29
00:07:59,372 --> 00:08:04,896
Det är en exempel på de döda maskinpågärderna i fjärilarna som skyddar Tunis och Bezerta.

30
00:08:05,576 --> 00:08:08,999
De visar hur svårt och långsiktigt våra arméer har gått i den sista kvällen i Afrika.

31
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:12,581
Men här finns evidens av de allvarliga strider som våra krig har gjort.

32
00:08:13,725 --> 00:08:19,208
Hard going, but harder still for Germans and Italians and theirs is the losing end of the battle.

33
00:08:19,247 --> 00:08:23,589
Here at Jebel al-Utia, our infantry are advancing again for the attack on Sugarloaf Hill.

34
00:08:24,290 --> 00:08:28,211
And again fresh batches of prisoners are being sent off to the rear, nearly all Germans.

35
00:08:28,872 --> 00:08:30,492
But in this sector there are also some Austrians.

36
00:08:30,512 --> 00:08:33,455
They were Austrian trenches in which our men took cover.

37
00:08:39,076 --> 00:08:41,357
Our tanks have wrought great havoc among the enemy guns.

38
00:08:41,946 --> 00:08:48,311
And it was here that two great British armies met again, the first and the eighth.

39
00:08:49,150 --> 00:08:56,777
And with them the French, commanded by the valiant general Leclerc, whose men are keeping alive the flickering flame of France's glory.

40
00:08:57,317 --> 00:09:02,600
And here another column is rolling forward to Cairoan, taken by our forces a few days after the fall of Sfax.

41
00:09:03,461 --> 00:09:07,144
One piece of evidence for those who still doubt the stories of Nazi oppression.

42
00:09:07,183 --> 00:09:11,226
Jews are now able to remove the Star of David, which they must wear wherever Germans rule.

43
00:09:12,149 --> 00:09:15,272
And these are the tanks which toured Britain during the Tanks Week campaign.

44
00:09:17,014 --> 00:09:19,115
So ended another stage in the Battle of Tunisia.

45
00:09:19,696 --> 00:09:24,860
General Montgomery in conference with General Alexander preparing the next great push on to Tunis.

46
00:09:24,879 --> 00:09:25,179
TUNIS

47
00:09:41,467 --> 00:09:46,611
Bombers landing at an aerodrome not far from Tunis are not in this case returning from a blitz over enemy lines.

48
00:09:46,731 --> 00:09:48,254
They carry airmines itself.

49
00:09:48,573 --> 00:09:51,596
Here, still in enemy occupation, we see no sign of life.

50
00:09:52,136 --> 00:09:54,599
No wonder, because our mastery was so complete.

51
00:09:55,239 --> 00:09:56,379
Figures are fantastic.

52
00:09:56,539 --> 00:10:00,043
2,000 sorties per day was quite a usual number for fighters and bombers.

53
00:10:00,102 --> 00:10:00,604
One day, 2,500 sorties.

54
00:10:00,624 --> 00:10:04,527
And over one sector of the axis lines, our aircraft flew at the rate of four planes every minute for a solid stretch of nine hours.

55
00:10:10,019 --> 00:10:20,283
Rather, the tanks and field artillery smashed into the enemy positions, pounding their strong points to pulp, shattering morale and paving the way for our infantry to make that swift, amazing victory.

56
00:10:20,323 --> 00:10:25,427
They have lost their sullen, contemptuous superiority.

57
00:10:25,447 --> 00:10:30,908
Now you'll notice from the signposts how we're getting closer to Tunis.

58
00:10:32,009 --> 00:10:37,772
Here at Matur, our men linked up with the Americans, although the main American victory pictures from Berserta have not yet been received.

59
00:10:38,870 --> 00:10:41,552
De här krigarna kommer nu in i större grupper.

60
00:10:41,572 --> 00:10:45,995
Prelude till Cape Bonn faller när de förvandlades i hela battaljonen.

61
00:10:46,015 --> 00:10:49,698
Nästan de enda salkiga är de här av Krak Hermann Göring-regimentet.

62
00:10:50,278 --> 00:10:53,660
De har skadat namnet Göring, som om han inte kunde göra det själv.

63
00:10:56,163 --> 00:10:57,224
Men du är här också.

64
00:10:58,065 --> 00:11:02,488
Nu är transport och tankar av första och sjätte armén rörande varje annan för att vara först till Tunis.

65
00:11:02,508 --> 00:11:04,028
De ställer vägen för att komma där.

66
00:11:04,836 --> 00:11:09,876
General Alexander berättar med den första arméns kommande, general Andersson.

67
00:11:11,618 --> 00:11:14,538
Och de sista förlångarna av framgången går under fötterna av fötterna.

68
00:11:14,618 --> 00:11:16,759
Medan artillerifjärden når ett nytt nivå.

69
00:11:16,778 --> 00:11:19,318
Från kriget är kvinnor och krigsbrytare fortfarande på väggen.

70
00:11:19,339 --> 00:11:20,538
Ja, han har en trofé när han kör med dem.

71
00:11:20,558 --> 00:11:29,260
Men många tyskar gick själva in i kapptiviteten, glada att vara utav det.

72
00:11:35,197 --> 00:11:36,277
Tunis är i sikt.

73
00:11:37,778 --> 00:11:40,458
Och på vägen är de skadade med kärlek och önskemål.

74
00:11:42,419 --> 00:11:43,559
Ja, deras också.

75
00:11:44,441 --> 00:11:47,361
Det är omöjligt att uppmärksamma så högt R.A.M.C.s arbete.

76
00:11:47,642 --> 00:11:48,422
Män av alla ranger.

77
00:11:48,922 --> 00:11:52,663
De har konstant påverkat märken under kriget och aldrig vävats.

78
00:11:52,683 --> 00:11:55,105
Här på utskottet av Tunis är kvinnorna lämna en hand.

79
00:11:55,125 --> 00:11:57,326
Det här är den berömda 7. armadivisionen som släppte pancerna från Egypten.

80
00:12:11,134 --> 00:12:14,456
En del av eleverna som kastar sig över dagar.

81
00:12:14,476 --> 00:12:16,398
Försäkringar för att bli först in.

82
00:12:17,018 --> 00:12:18,198
Det är inte helt över.

83
00:12:18,239 --> 00:12:20,080
Frågorna är fortfarande många.

84
00:12:20,421 --> 00:12:21,660
Och de har alla fått.

85
00:12:24,643 --> 00:12:25,823
Nu för infanteriet.

86
00:12:25,844 --> 00:12:27,445
Den unglösa momenten av livet.

87
00:12:27,485 --> 00:12:29,647
Och fortfarande fler frisörer.

88
00:12:29,687 --> 00:12:33,448
Och den germanska major och hans staff blev frisörer också.

89
00:12:33,489 --> 00:12:34,710
Som alla andra ratar.

90
00:12:38,878 --> 00:12:41,059
The Italians are so pleased about it they're even singing.

91
00:12:41,379 --> 00:12:45,842
Meanwhile on the outskirts of the city in a quiet street is a quiet man who still has a job to do.

92
00:12:46,302 --> 00:12:48,044
Cleaning up the remains in Cape Bond.

93
00:12:52,927 --> 00:12:56,610
But the long procession goes on through a hysterical, crazily excited crowd.

94
00:12:56,710 --> 00:13:00,513
This must always rank as one of our greatest moments so far in this war.

95
00:13:01,212 --> 00:13:02,913
Distant indeed are the grim days of 1940.

96
00:13:04,062 --> 00:13:08,062
This is a reward for every man and woman who refuse to believe that Britain could lose.

97
00:13:08,102 --> 00:13:09,243
This is the first installment in payment for your faith.

98
00:13:09,263 --> 00:13:10,764
You who have fought and you who have worked to make the tools of victory.

99
00:13:10,783 --> 00:13:11,663
This is your hour and these are your men.
